Honest caveats:

This assumes Zach adds the warmup short-circuit. If he can't for a few days, don't panic — the warmer still works, it just runs the full flow every 5 min and creates some background query load. Not ideal but not broken.
If cold calls are still >2s after this, the query is genuinely slow even on a warm DB (unlikely, since warm queries were 52–131ms), OR the warmer isn't landing on the right container. At that point, next lever is Provisioned Concurrency (1 instance). But start here.
lambda_function_name output — I'm using module.soap_verification_lambda.lambda_function_name in the permission block. Confirm your lambda module exposes that output. If it doesn't, you may need lambda_function_arn and let the permission derive the name from it, or check the module code.

